// Import/Creation

// All creation endpoints work in UI (GUI) mode only — they hand the parsed entry to the
// running JabRef instance, which appends it to a real open tab.
//
// The `{id}` path segment selects the *target* library:
//   * `current`                       -> the currently active tab (no tab switch)
//   * `<filename>-<uniquePrefix>`      -> that specific open library; JabRef switches to its
//                                         tab first, then appends (see the `### Get the list of
//                                         all libraries` request above for the exact ids)
//   * an unknown / closed id          -> 404 Not Found
//
// To target a specific library, run `GET /libraries`, copy the id of the library you want, and
// paste it into the `@libraryId` variable below. IntelliJ's HTTP client substitutes it into the
// `{{libraryId}}` placeholders. The demo id is shown as an example; replace it with one of yours.

###

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries

###

@libraryId = demo

### Add BibTeX to the active library (`current`)

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/current/entries
Content-Type: application/x-bibtex

@article{demo,
  title = {Added by REST}
}

### Add BibTeX to a specific open library (switches to its tab first)

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/{{libraryId}}/entries
Content-Type: application/x-bibtex

@article{demoTargeted,
  title = {Added by REST to a specific library}
}

### Add BibTeX and also assign it to a group (created if missing)

// The `group` query parameter additionally files the entry under a top-level group of that name.

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/current/entries?group=Imported%20via%20REST
Content-Type: application/x-bibtex

@article{demoGrouped,
  title = {Added by REST and grouped}
}

### Add a plain-text citation (parsed via the configured plain-citation parser)

// Consumes text/plain. The text is run through the parser selected in
// Preferences > Import (e.g. Grobid or the LLM parser), then appended.

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/current/entries
Content-Type: text/plain

Smith, J. (2020). On the nature of chocolate. Journal of Sweets, 12(3), 45-67.

### Import RIS to the active library (`current`)

// Any content type other than BibTeX / text/plain is written to a temp file and imported
// through JabRef's format detection — RIS, EndNote, etc. all take this path.

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/current/entries
Content-Type: application/x-research-info-systems

TY  - CHAP
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/09/10
Y2  - 2015/11/06
M1  - 0
DO  - doi:10.1201/b19107-2
UR  - http://dx.doi.org/10.1201/b19107-2
N1  - doi:10.1201/b19107-2
AU  - Catarina Barata
AU  - MEmre Celebi
AU  - JorgeS Marques
SP  - 1-22
TI  - Toward a Robust Analysis of Dermoscopy Images Acquired under Different Conditions
T2  - Dermoscopy Image Analysis
T3  - Digital Imaging and Computer Vision
SN  - 978-1-4822-5326-9
PB  - CRC Press
ER  -

### Import RIS to a specific open library

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/{{libraryId}}/entries
Content-Type: application/x-research-info-systems

TY  - JOUR
AU  - Doe, Jane
TI  - Targeted RIS import
PY  - 2021
ER  -

###

# Creation — error cases

### Add to an unknown library id -> 404 Not Found

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/does-not-exist/entries
Content-Type: application/x-bibtex

@article{x, title = {nope}}

### Add empty BibTeX -> 400 Bad Request

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/{{libraryId}}/entries
Content-Type: application/x-bibtex


## Cached plain-citation lookup, then add

// Two-step flow so the (possibly expensive) parse happens once:
//   1. POST .../citations/lookup parses the text, reports whether it already exists in the
//      target / other open libraries, and returns a `parserCacheKey`.
//   2. POST .../citations/<parserCacheKey> appends the cached parse to the target library.
//
// Copy the `parserCacheKey` from the lookup response into `@cacheKey` before running step 2.

### Step 1: look up a citation

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/{{libraryId}}/citations/lookup
Content-Type: text/plain

Smith, J. (2020). On the nature of chocolate. Journal of Sweets, 12(3), 45-67.

### Step 2: add the cached citation (201 Created; 200 already-exists; 410 Gone if expired)

@cacheKey = paste-parserCacheKey-from-the-lookup-response

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/current/citations/{{cacheKey}}

### Lookup against an unknown library id -> 404 Not Found

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/does-not-exist/citations/lookup
Content-Type: text/plain

Smith, J. (2020). On the nature of chocolate. Journal of Sweets, 12(3), 45-67.
